definition.value: The Concurrent With operator asserts that an event on the left-hand side has the same effective time as an event on the right-hand side. In other words, both of the following statements must be true: (a) The start date/time of an event on the left-hand side is equal to the start date/time of an event on the right-hand side. (b) The end date/time of the same left-hand side event is equal to the end date/time of the same right-hand side event. Note: Since the QDM defines timing comparisons to have a default precision of one minute, the starts of the events must be within one minute of each other and the ends of the events must be within one minute of each other. This may limit the number of use cases in which this temporal operator is applicable.

Note: Since the QDM defines timing comparisons to have a default precision of one minute, the starts of the events must be within one minute of each other and the ends of the events must be within one minute of each other. definition.value: The Overlaps operator asserts that there exists some point in time at which the event on the left- hand side is effective at the same time as the event on the right-hand side. Since events can have a left overlap, right overlap, inner overlap, or outer overlap, the Overlaps operator uses the start date/time and end/time of each event to determine if there is overlap.
